From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Conda Forge <conda-forge@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Exclude aarch64-use variants from monolithic library

The memcpy_aarch64-use and memset_aarch64-use libraries cause duplicate
symbol definitions when linked into the monolithic library because they
compile the same source files as memcpy_aarch64 and memset_aarch64.

---
 folly/external/aor/CMakeLists.txt | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/folly/external/aor/CMakeLists.txt b/folly/external/aor/CMakeLists.txt
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/folly/external/aor/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/folly/external/aor/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -35,6 +35,7 @@ endif()
 
 folly_add_library(
   NAME memcpy_aarch64-use
+  EXCLUDE_FROM_MONOLITH
   SRCS
     memcpy-advsimd.S
     memcpy-armv8.S
@@ -58,6 +59,7 @@ endif()
 
 folly_add_library(
   NAME memset_aarch64-use
+  EXCLUDE_FROM_MONOLITH
   SRCS
     memset-advsimd.S
     memset-mops.S
